attributes.background:
The food waste caused by multisaves/BOGOF (“bulk promotions”) is appalling.  We propose:

(i) bulk promotions are not permitted on perishable food;
(ii) increasing the price for a single item around the same time as the bulk promotion is deceitful and should not be permitted;
(iii) the price for a single item should be clearly displayed alongside the bulk promotion;
(iv) products should not be on bulk promotions indefinitely, but rather for a limited period of time (c.f. sales where shops are not meant to promote a product as being on sale indefinitely).

The practice is also simply unfair for single people who cannot benefit from promotions.  Even for larger households, promoting goods by X% off rather than the equivalent bulk promotion, would benefit larger households to the same extent as the present bulk promotions.  Bulk promotions also make shopping more confusing – trying to figure out what is in and what is out of the promotion; calculating the single item cost, the judgement of whether you would make use of an extra item, and ensuring it is honoured at the till…
